reviews.text: Great park with great displays and thrilling rides. Cable car is a amazing way to get from the one half of the park to the other.can be hard to get round as on so many different levels but worth the effort. On busy days fast pass is a must.
It was a nice place, but sad to say we did not enjoy due that having storm signal 8 they need to close the whole park.. 😢

I love this place. I actually enjoyed my stay visit here more than Disneyland. The place is bigger and the cable car is a must. 
The aquariums are magnificent and the sand castles are amazing too. The games and amusements places are perfect for kids and adult.
The summit is perfect for photographers too. I enjoyed going here even just by myself. 
I highly recommend this place.

For those who likes animal, and for those who likes thrill rides... This is it!!
This is the place for you to go!
So much fun and thrilling rides!!
The roller coasters are quite intimidating for some, but for those who are up for the thrill go try all the bigger coaster.
And the animal, they're awesome!! Especially the aquarium, it's so enormous its like walking under the sea!! The grand aquarium and Shark mystique are a must go! There's even penguins here!!
The dolphin show are fun too, the dolphins really can jump very high!
It's not recommended for older people though because the terrain here is somewhat hilly and need more energy to walk the whole park in one day (especially on peak season).
The price here are reasonable compared to D-land, and the merchandise prices are a lot cheaper too!
Love this place, and want to go back here next time i go to hongkong!
Staff is very nice..... but too many tourists and the tourists are very rude ....but anyway the zoo inside still great , and they protect the animal very well , that’s something we appreciate a lot
